UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='Garrosh is brash and speaks harshly, but his intentions are good. In time, he will grow to see your people as a valuable ally.$B$BI am awaiting reports about recent Alliance activity in Durotar, but they haven\'t arrived yet. Would you be willing to visit Razor Hill and ask him for the reports in person? The easiest way to get there is by wind rider. Doras, Orgrimmar\'s wind rider master will let you use one of his wind riders for a small fee. Look for him on the rise north of the Valley of Strength.' WHERE `word_id` = 182381; -- locales_quest - details : entry=26803
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='Garwal was not a worg at all! I know of these creatures... they are called worgen.$B$BBut, Ulfang indicated that it came south from the Grizzly Hills? Odd. There aren\'t any worgen there.$B$BI thank you for helping to restore Ulfang to his proper place amongst his pack. Now we both will be able to sleep peacefully.$B$BPlease, you must accept this as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE `word_id` = 156359; -- locales_quest - offerrewardtext : entry=11324
UPDATE `trans_words` SET `content_loc6`='Garwal was not a worg at all! The thing you describe him turning into sounds a lot like a worgen!$B$BBut, Ulfang said that it came south from the Grizzly Hills? Odd. There aren\'t any worgen there.$B$BI thank you for helping to restore Ulfang to his proper place amongst his pack. Now we both will be able to sleep peacefully.$B$BPlease, you must accept this as a sign of gratitude.' WHERE `word_id` = 156365; -- locales_quest - offerrewardtext : entry=11326
